Heat oven to 350 degrees F (325 degrees F for glass dish). In medium bowl, combine flour and sugar; cut in butter until crumbly. Press firmly on bottom of 13x9-inch baking pan. Bake 15 minutes. In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk, egg and extract; mix well. Stir in toffee pieces and almonds. Spread mixture evenly over prepared crust. Bake 25 minutes or until golden brown. Cool. Cut into bars. Store leftovers covered in refrigerator.